    <h2>FAQs About Queen Anne Chocolate Covered Cherries and Gluten</h2>

    <div class="faq">
        <h3>1. Are Queen Anne Chocolate Covered Cherries gluten-free?</h3>
        <p>Queen Anne Chocolate Covered Cherries do not contain gluten ingredients, but they are not certified gluten-free. There may be a risk of cross-contamination during manufacturing.</p>

        <h3>2. Can individuals with celiac disease eat Queen Anne Chocolate Covered Cherries?</h3>
        <p>Individuals with celiac disease should exercise caution. While the product does not contain gluten ingredients, the lack of a gluten-free certification means there is a potential risk of cross-contamination.</p>

        <h3>3. Does Queen Anne provide allergen information?</h3>
        <p>Yes, Queen Anne provides allergen information on their packaging. However, they do not specifically label their chocolate-covered cherries as gluten-free.</p>

        <h3>4. What should I do if I have a severe gluten sensitivity?</h3>
        <p>If you have a severe gluten sensitivity or celiac disease, it is best to contact the manufacturer directly for detailed information about their production processes and potential cross-contamination risks.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>

    <p>Queen Anne Chocolate Covered Cherries are a delightful treat that many enjoy, but for those with gluten sensitivities or celiac disease, the question of whether they are gluten-free is an important one. While the product does not contain gluten ingredients, the lack of a gluten-free certification and the potential for cross-contamination during manufacturing mean that individuals with severe gluten sensitivities should proceed with caution. Always check the packaging for allergen information and consider reaching out to the manufacturer for more detailed insights. By taking these steps, you can make informed decisions about whether Queen Anne Chocolate Covered Cherries are a safe choice for your dietary needs.</p>

